1
00:00:08,577 --> 00:00:09,677
Professor Ahn.

2
00:00:10,107 --> 00:00:12,076
- Hold on. Today...
- Sandwiches?

3
00:00:12,077 --> 00:00:14,216
We're starting our episode with some food today.

4
00:00:14,217 --> 00:00:15,516
Their sandwiches are good.

5
00:00:15,517 --> 00:00:17,416
- Their sandwiches are tasty.
- They are.

6
00:00:17,417 --> 00:00:18,956
- Hello.
- Hello.

7
00:00:18,957 --> 00:00:20,616
- We're going to...
- This looks good.

8
00:00:20,617 --> 00:00:23,756
get two sandwiches to go for our guests today.

9
00:00:23,757 --> 00:00:25,256
What a filling breakfast.

10
00:00:25,257 --> 00:00:27,226
- Is this a new sandwich?
- Yes, it is.

11
00:00:27,227 --> 00:00:28,696
- I should get this.
- Okay.

12
00:00:28,697 --> 00:00:30,127
- I'll take the bulgogi sandwich.
- Sure.

13
00:00:30,327 --> 00:00:31,997
I want the egg mayo sandwich.

14
00:00:32,267 --> 00:00:34,267
- We should get some to go.
- We should.

15
00:00:34,837 --> 00:00:36,537
Which one should we pick?

16
00:00:37,237 --> 00:00:39,476
- We don't know who they are.
- We don't.

17
00:00:39,477 --> 00:00:41,747
- I don't know what they'll like.
- We have to know who they are.

18
00:00:42,347 --> 00:00:43,977
- Why won't you tell us, though?
- Right.

19
00:00:44,347 --> 00:00:45,476
- Is it that important?
- I just don't want to tell you.

20
00:00:45,477 --> 00:00:46,477
You don't want to tell us?

21
00:00:46,478 --> 00:00:49,347
- Then we won't talk about them.
- My gosh.

22
00:00:49,517 --> 00:00:51,717
We'll take one traditional sandwich...

23
00:00:51,917 --> 00:00:53,556
and one bulgogi sandwich.

24
00:00:53,557 --> 00:00:55,386
- We'll take them to go.
- Sure.

25
00:00:55,387 --> 00:00:57,156
- I bet they're good.
- It looks good.

26
00:00:57,157 --> 00:00:59,556
This sandwich franchise is popular in college neighborhoods.

27
00:00:59,557 --> 00:01:01,396
Right. Around Sejong University...

28
00:01:01,397 --> 00:01:03,667
- There is, right? Professor Ahn.
- What?

29
00:01:04,097 --> 00:01:06,437
- Is there?
- He brought that up again.

30
00:01:07,137 --> 00:01:08,706
A lot of our colleagues...

31
00:01:08,707 --> 00:01:10,466
- Right. Many actors eat this too.
- eat these sandwiches.

32
00:01:10,467 --> 00:01:12,007
- Right.
- Yes.

33
00:01:13,277 --> 00:01:15,706
The sandwiches are warm since they are toasted in the oven.

34
00:01:15,707 --> 00:01:18,347
- Gosh, the baguette is so moist.
- It's tasty.

35
00:01:19,317 --> 00:01:20,516
We have to eat it on the spot.

36
00:01:20,517 --> 00:01:22,987
(Quickly having a bite when it's warm)

37
00:01:24,617 --> 00:01:25,617
(Humming)

38
00:01:27,287 --> 00:01:28,426
Gosh, it's so good.

39
00:01:28,427 --> 00:01:30,687
(Yeon Seok has a big bite too.)

40
00:01:32,957 --> 00:01:33,997
It's good.

41
00:01:35,627 --> 00:01:37,026
(Establishing eye contact)

42
00:01:37,027 --> 00:01:38,297
- Isn't it good?
- It's good.

43
00:01:39,267 --> 00:01:41,397
- Dip it in the soup?
- Of course.

44
00:01:41,637 --> 00:01:43,637
I'm getting it all over the place. I'll keep it clean.

45
00:01:45,837 --> 00:01:47,507
Gosh, look. It's steaming.

46
00:01:48,347 --> 00:01:51,407
(Food tastes the best when it's warm.)

47
00:01:51,947 --> 00:01:54,016
Everyone will like it. It's so good.

48
00:01:54,017 --> 00:01:55,347
(Sandwiches make the perfect breakfast.)

49
00:01:55,687 --> 00:01:57,047
It goes really well with the bread.

50
00:01:57,547 --> 00:01:59,256
We ordered two sandwiches to go earlier.

51
00:01:59,257 --> 00:02:00,957
- Let's take them with us.
- We should go.

52
00:02:01,257 --> 00:02:03,086
- Let's go and meet our friends.
- Let's do that.

53
00:02:03,087 --> 00:02:04,157
(They set out to meet Whenever Friends.)

54
00:02:04,997 --> 00:02:06,196
(Around the same time)

55
00:02:06,197 --> 00:02:09,826
This park is called Gajaeul or something.

56
00:02:09,827 --> 00:02:10,896
- Right.
- Yes.

57
00:02:10,897 --> 00:02:12,336
(Today's spare time, Gajwa)

58
00:02:12,337 --> 00:02:13,996
I see. This is the place.

59
00:02:13,997 --> 00:02:15,907
I used to pass by here on a motorcycle.

60
00:02:16,507 --> 00:02:18,806
So Jae Seok doesn't know we're coming today?

61
00:02:18,807 --> 00:02:20,037
It's about time you surprised him.

62
00:02:20,637 --> 00:02:24,176
I'm not sure if they will like the sandwiches.

63
00:02:24,177 --> 00:02:26,677
Some people these days don't drink soda.

64
00:02:26,877 --> 00:02:29,347
- I think I see them over there.
- Are they already here?

65
00:02:30,117 --> 00:02:31,887
- It's chilly today.
- Yes.

66
00:02:32,287 --> 00:02:33,917
I didn't wear a shirt underneath.

67
00:02:34,417 --> 00:02:35,657
I see two guys.

68
00:02:36,187 --> 00:02:38,087
I don't think they're handsome.

69
00:02:38,227 --> 00:02:39,427
"Handsome?"

70
00:02:40,957 --> 00:02:42,167
Wait, is it Ssaebssaeb?

71
00:02:42,527 --> 00:02:43,567
- It's Ssaebssaeb.
- Gosh.

72
00:02:44,497 --> 00:02:45,697
Hello.

73
00:02:45,937 --> 00:02:47,897
(Today's Whenever Friends: Yang Se Chan and Yang Se Hyeong)

74
00:02:48,037 --> 00:02:50,736
- It's Se Hyeong and Se Chan.
- They aren't actors.

75
00:02:50,737 --> 00:02:52,377
- Hello.
- Se Hyeong and Se Chan.

76
00:02:53,137 --> 00:02:54,777
My gosh, Se Hyeong.

77
00:02:54,877 --> 00:02:55,877
Se Hyeong.

78
00:02:55,878 --> 00:02:57,776
- It's been a while.
- Se Chan.

79
00:02:57,777 --> 00:02:59,816
I called you yesterday. This is why you didn't pick up.

80
00:02:59,817 --> 00:03:01,547
I didn't tell you on purpose just in case it was a secret.

81
00:03:01,947 --> 00:03:02,947
- I had no idea.
- That's why.

82
00:03:02,948 --> 00:03:04,717
I didn't want to ruin the surprise. So I didn't tell him.

83
00:03:05,557 --> 00:03:07,156
- Let's sit down. By the way, - Okay.

84
00:03:07,157 --> 00:03:08,857
- Here? What do you think?
- we bought some sandwiches.

85
00:03:09,057 --> 00:03:10,886
- Really?
- They are very delicious.

86
00:03:10,887 --> 00:03:12,597
- They are the perfect breakfast.
- Yes.

87
00:03:12,697 --> 00:03:14,197
- It's warm.
- It's the traditional sandwich.

88
00:03:15,527 --> 00:03:16,896
- The traditional sandwich.
- Yes.

89
00:03:16,897 --> 00:03:18,336
- Gosh.
- Isn't it good?

90
00:03:18,337 --> 00:03:19,437
Yes.

91
00:03:19,967 --> 00:03:21,607
We just bought it. So it's good.

92
00:03:22,707 --> 00:03:23,707
(Getting up)

93
00:03:24,137 --> 00:03:25,207
Wait, no.

94
00:03:25,307 --> 00:03:27,107
I thought you were eating the parchment paper too.

95
00:03:28,377 --> 00:03:30,446
Se Hyeong stopped eating paper now.

96
00:03:30,447 --> 00:03:32,317
- He quit?
- He used to eat some paper before.

97
00:03:32,377 --> 00:03:33,947
I used to eat it when I got hungry.

98
00:03:34,217 --> 00:03:36,016
- He's making good money now.
- Not anymore.

99
00:03:36,017 --> 00:03:37,017
- So he doesn't eat paper anymore.
- Right.

100
00:03:37,018 --> 00:03:38,917
- You don't eat sand now, right?
- I don't.

101
00:03:39,217 --> 00:03:41,157
Now, I dust off the sand.

102
00:03:42,357 --> 00:03:45,296
I don't know why we ate so much random stuff when we were kids.

103
00:03:45,297 --> 00:03:47,957
Have you not tried eating the eraser crumbs?

104
00:03:48,157 --> 00:03:50,226
- Why would you eat that?
- I used to taste them.

105
00:03:50,227 --> 00:03:51,697
To see how chewy they were.

106
00:03:51,867 --> 00:03:52,996
You haven't tried them.

107
00:03:52,997 --> 00:03:54,237
- For real?
- Yes.

108
00:03:54,367 --> 00:03:57,407
I used to chew on them little by little back in the day.

109
00:03:57,837 --> 00:03:59,477
Why are you distancing yourself from me?

110
00:04:00,807 --> 00:04:03,247
- I didn't eat eraser crumbs.
- I did that back in the day.

111
00:04:04,447 --> 00:04:07,646
- You dolled yourself up, Se Chan.
- Yes, I did.

112
00:04:07,647 --> 00:04:11,086
- Yes. Of course.
- You're wearing a tie for once.

113
00:04:11,087 --> 00:04:12,186
- I ought to wear a tie.
- I see.

114
00:04:12,187 --> 00:04:13,616
You've been dressing up lately.

115
00:04:13,617 --> 00:04:15,027
What about you, Se Hyeong?

116
00:04:15,227 --> 00:04:16,826
Actually,

117
00:04:16,827 --> 00:04:20,527
I'm not good at matching colors for my outfits.

118
00:04:20,797 --> 00:04:22,666
- I don't have many clothes at home.
- Is that so?

119
00:04:22,667 --> 00:04:24,166
- You're not interested in fashion.
- I'm not.

120
00:04:24,167 --> 00:04:27,537
That's why when I see him from afar, he's a total midlifer.

121
00:04:27,937 --> 00:04:30,507
He wears the ultimate outfit of midlifers.

122
00:04:30,667 --> 00:04:33,537
He only wears comfortable shoes and pants.

123
00:04:33,737 --> 00:04:35,777
Once you start wearing comfortable outfits, you can't stop.

124
00:04:36,107 --> 00:04:39,077
A long time ago, he often wore golf clothes when he went out.

125
00:04:39,147 --> 00:04:40,476
All of his friends know what I mean.

126
00:04:40,477 --> 00:04:42,587
He wore a hat to go with the outfit. I was embarrassed when he did that.

127
00:04:43,117 --> 00:04:44,517
Let me explain. I...

128
00:04:45,457 --> 00:04:47,016
But I couldn't tell him...

129
00:04:47,017 --> 00:04:48,456
to dress better.

130
00:04:48,457 --> 00:04:50,426
I'm not stylish either.

131
00:04:50,427 --> 00:04:52,596
But he only wore golf clothes.

132
00:04:52,597 --> 00:04:54,857
I'm only bringing this up now.

133
00:04:55,027 --> 00:04:56,697
I was embarrassed of him before he got braces.

134
00:04:57,397 --> 00:04:58,566
I'm only bringing it up now.

135
00:04:58,567 --> 00:05:00,836
- But that was 15 or 20 years ago.
- Okay.

136
00:05:00,837 --> 00:05:02,367
- But you were still embarrassing.
- Right.

137
00:05:02,537 --> 00:05:04,367
I let you tag along, but you looked like a piranha.

138
00:05:05,837 --> 00:05:07,876
How could you call your brother a piranha?

139
00:05:07,877 --> 00:05:09,276
(Before Se Chan got his protruded teeth corrected)

140
00:05:09,277 --> 00:05:10,707
"Where are you going?"

141
00:05:11,777 --> 00:05:13,717
Calling your brother a piranha is a bit mean.

142
00:05:14,217 --> 00:05:15,617
- A piranha?
- I love piranhas.

143
00:05:16,347 --> 00:05:17,616
- I love them.
- That's why, right?

144
00:05:17,617 --> 00:05:18,687
Yes. I love them.

145
00:05:19,357 --> 00:05:21,686
By the way, when Se Hyeong is with Se Chan,

146
00:05:21,687 --> 00:05:23,356
he's somewhat of...

147
00:05:23,357 --> 00:05:24,996
- a charismatic brother.
- Right.

148
00:05:24,997 --> 00:05:26,897
- He's a big brother indeed.
- He does act like one.

149
00:05:27,057 --> 00:05:28,927
- When we were kids, - Yes.

150
00:05:29,227 --> 00:05:31,026
both of our parents used to work.

151
00:05:31,027 --> 00:05:33,337
They often left us alone for 3 or 4 days,

152
00:05:33,537 --> 00:05:35,167
sometimes up to a week.

153
00:05:35,307 --> 00:05:37,207
They had no choice because they had to make money.

154
00:05:37,407 --> 00:05:39,737
That's why our mother made sure...

155
00:05:39,837 --> 00:05:41,847
we respected the hierarchy between us.

156
00:05:42,207 --> 00:05:44,446
- She ensured there was a hierarchy.
- Yes.

157
00:05:44,447 --> 00:05:45,717
Se Chan had to listen to me.

158
00:05:45,877 --> 00:05:48,886
And I had to step up and protect my brother...

159
00:05:48,887 --> 00:05:50,146
- when he was...
- You had to keep him safe.

160
00:05:50,147 --> 00:05:51,287
in trouble.

161
00:05:51,787 --> 00:05:54,617
When you were kids, Se Hyeong probably scolded you.

162
00:05:54,987 --> 00:05:57,626
But when you were about the same height,

163
00:05:57,627 --> 00:05:59,496
you must have tried to stand up to him.

164
00:05:59,497 --> 00:06:01,027
We had never been around the same height.

165
00:06:01,197 --> 00:06:02,497
I had always been taller.

166
00:06:04,227 --> 00:06:06,136
- Why...
- Ever since we were kids...

167
00:06:06,137 --> 00:06:07,296
Ever since we were kids,

168
00:06:07,297 --> 00:06:09,067
- I was slightly taller.
- Really?

169
00:06:09,337 --> 00:06:11,466
That's when he developed an inferiority complex...

170
00:06:11,467 --> 00:06:13,007
and became an angry person.

171
00:06:13,177 --> 00:06:16,377
"I'm older. How come I'm shorter?" He tried to be tough.

172
00:06:17,747 --> 00:06:19,846
I have a brother too.

173
00:06:19,847 --> 00:06:21,146
He's two years older than me.

174
00:06:21,147 --> 00:06:23,387
I had always been shorter than him.

175
00:06:24,147 --> 00:06:26,416
But in high school, I became as tall as he was.

176
00:06:26,417 --> 00:06:28,857
- Did you stand up to him then?
- I disobeyed him.

177
00:06:28,987 --> 00:06:30,427
Then he gave me a good beating.

178
00:06:31,857 --> 00:06:33,826
When we were kids,

179
00:06:33,827 --> 00:06:35,327
- we fought a lot.
- We used to fight a lot.

180
00:06:35,527 --> 00:06:37,697
- We fought physically.
- Really?

181
00:06:37,797 --> 00:06:39,096
We got into physical fights.

182
00:06:39,097 --> 00:06:40,896
Because we fought so often, our mother...

183
00:06:40,897 --> 00:06:42,906
- bought us gloves. She really did.
- She got you gloves?

184
00:06:42,907 --> 00:06:43,907
- So you could fight?
- Yes.

185
00:06:43,908 --> 00:06:45,436
- So we could just fight.
- Really?

186
00:06:45,437 --> 00:06:47,237
- "Wear them when you fight."
- "Have at it."

187
00:06:47,537 --> 00:06:49,106
(As they fought and goofed around all the time, )

188
00:06:49,107 --> 00:06:51,206
They were quite the famous brothers in Dongducheon.

189
00:06:51,207 --> 00:06:53,447
(they were known as the hardest sons to raise.)

190
00:06:53,677 --> 00:06:56,217
And their mother is an impressive lady too.

191
00:06:56,317 --> 00:06:57,587
She's part of the military reserve force.

192
00:06:57,847 --> 00:07:00,587
- As a woman.
- She completed the training too.

193
00:07:00,787 --> 00:07:03,587
How did she end up completing the reserve forces training?

194
00:07:03,787 --> 00:07:06,057
In case a war broke out,

195
00:07:06,227 --> 00:07:07,696
- she wanted to be able...
- Right.

196
00:07:07,697 --> 00:07:09,166
to take down 2 or 3 people.

197
00:07:09,167 --> 00:07:10,396
I'm serious.

198
00:07:10,397 --> 00:07:13,096
She wanted to handle at least 2 or 3 soldiers charging at her.

199
00:07:13,097 --> 00:07:14,566
- She wanted to protect her family.
- Right.

200
00:07:14,567 --> 00:07:16,536
But that's the truth. I'm not trying to be funny.

201
00:07:16,537 --> 00:07:18,237
- That's what she said.
- She meant it.

202
00:07:18,407 --> 00:07:19,676
She's so cool.

203
00:07:19,677 --> 00:07:22,477
Our family has a group chatroom.

204
00:07:22,607 --> 00:07:24,447
Other families share photos of food or flowers.

205
00:07:24,547 --> 00:07:25,847
She shares photos of her throwing grenades.

206
00:07:27,377 --> 00:07:28,686
- Or her saluting.
- In her military uniform.

207
00:07:28,687 --> 00:07:30,716
- Right, those photos.
- Or her holding a rifle.

208
00:07:30,717 --> 00:07:31,746
(A photo of their mom)

209
00:07:31,747 --> 00:07:32,956
She's Rambo.

210
00:07:32,957 --> 00:07:35,287
(Mom Rambo is stronger than anyone.)

211
00:07:35,987 --> 00:07:39,897
I was wondering who had ties to Namgajwa-dong.

212
00:07:40,027 --> 00:07:41,096
- It was the Yangs.
- When I saw them,

213
00:07:41,097 --> 00:07:42,166
I connected the dots.

214
00:07:42,167 --> 00:07:44,227
We moved into this neighborhood in 2016.

215
00:07:44,527 --> 00:07:46,496
- For four years.
- This neighborhood had good energy.

216
00:07:46,497 --> 00:07:49,406
- Many of our colleagues live here.
- That's right.

217
00:07:49,407 --> 00:07:52,536
- Really?
- Kang Jae Jun will move here soon.

218
00:07:52,537 --> 00:07:53,736
- Really?
- Yes.

219
00:07:53,737 --> 00:07:56,146
- Moon Se Yoon lives here.
- Se Yoon lives here.

220
00:07:56,147 --> 00:07:57,346
- Yoo Se Yoon lives here too.
- Yoo Se Yoon lives here.

221
00:07:57,347 --> 00:07:59,677
- Really? A lot of them live here.
- Many celebrities live here.

222
00:07:59,817 --> 00:08:03,116
- It's very close to Sangam-dong.
- It's close to TV stations.

223
00:08:03,117 --> 00:08:05,156
- Directors and writers live here.
- It's great.

224
00:08:05,157 --> 00:08:08,886
- Exactly.
- Actually, when we lived here...

225
00:08:08,887 --> 00:08:10,186
- Things worked out for you.
- Right.

226
00:08:10,187 --> 00:08:12,626
Our careers took off and we won many awards.

227
00:08:12,627 --> 00:08:15,267
The year after that, we moved out, and Se Yoon moved into our house.

228
00:08:15,327 --> 00:08:17,126
- Then he won the Grand Award.
- He won the Grand Award.

229
00:08:17,127 --> 00:08:18,466
(He won the Grand Award after moving to Gajwa.)

230
00:08:18,467 --> 00:08:19,496
There's good energy...

231
00:08:19,497 --> 00:08:20,937
- for entertainers.
- There's good energy.

232
00:08:21,367 --> 00:08:23,036
This is a nice neighborhood. It's good for entertainers.

233
00:08:23,037 --> 00:08:24,136
Then we can look forward...

234
00:08:24,137 --> 00:08:26,076
- to today's filming.
- Exactly. There's good energy...

235
00:08:26,077 --> 00:08:28,437
for entertainers here in Namgajwa-dong.

236
00:08:28,577 --> 00:08:31,576
You guys have played a lot of games while starring on variety shows.

237
00:08:31,577 --> 00:08:33,517
- We have all sorts of tricks.
- Right.

238
00:08:33,817 --> 00:08:35,946
I don't know what games we're going to play today.

239
00:08:35,947 --> 00:08:39,356
A long time ago, I used to play ddakji games.

240
00:08:39,357 --> 00:08:42,656
- Then there was a ddakji called LD.
- Lucky Ddakji.

241
00:08:42,657 --> 00:08:43,856
It's the most cherished...

242
00:08:43,857 --> 00:08:45,056
- and the best one.
- It's a ddakji.

243
00:08:45,057 --> 00:08:47,826
It takes days to make the Lucky Ddakji.

244
00:08:47,827 --> 00:08:49,996
- Why?
- Let me explain.

245
00:08:49,997 --> 00:08:51,896
I would fold the ddakji out of calendar paper...

246
00:08:51,897 --> 00:08:53,637
- and soak it with water.
- Okay.

