00:51:03,330 --> 00:51:04,829
- We're crossing?
- We have to cross?

1495
00:51:04,830 --> 00:51:05,900
Yes, and we take a bus there.

1496
00:51:08,270 --> 00:51:09,769
- Hey.
- It was a joke.

1497
00:51:09,770 --> 00:51:10,770
- It was, right?
- Yes.

1498
00:51:10,771 --> 00:51:12,070
We're sensitive about jokes right now.

1499
00:51:12,900 --> 00:51:14,299
Don't make jokes without thinking.

1500
00:51:14,300 --> 00:51:15,570
- The cameramen laughed.
- We're on the edge.

1501
00:51:15,640 --> 00:51:17,009
- But they laughed.
- We're all on the edge.

1502
00:51:17,010 --> 00:51:18,039
- We are.
- Yes.

1503
00:51:18,040 --> 00:51:19,779
- But I got a laugh.
- Fine.

1504
00:51:19,780 --> 00:51:20,810
To the right.

1505
00:51:21,510 --> 00:51:22,550
Here.

1506
00:51:23,210 --> 00:51:24,549
- I like that.
- And they have tables.

1507
00:51:24,550 --> 00:51:25,619
- Great.
- It looks nice.

1508
00:51:25,620 --> 00:51:26,979
- This is...
- Good afternoon.

1509
00:51:26,980 --> 00:51:28,049
- Can we eat here?
- Sure.

1510
00:51:28,050 --> 00:51:29,050
We're four people.

1511
00:51:29,150 --> 00:51:30,249
Let's play a game before we go in.

1512
00:51:30,250 --> 00:51:32,219
Yes, we have to pay first. Let's play a game first.

1513
00:51:32,220 --> 00:51:34,220
On the count of three,

1514
00:51:34,590 --> 00:51:35,830
you'll either stand or sit.

1515
00:51:36,260 --> 00:51:37,429
If you're in the minority, you pass.

1516
00:51:37,430 --> 00:51:38,799
- If you're in the minority?
- Yes.

1517
00:51:38,800 --> 00:51:39,900
- Okay.
- Okay?

1518
00:51:40,630 --> 00:51:41,970
- We go on the count of three.
- Okay.

1519
00:51:42,570 --> 00:51:44,430
- In 1, 2, 3.
- In 1, 2, 3.

1520
00:51:44,640 --> 00:51:45,970
It's a tie.

1521
00:51:46,770 --> 00:51:48,770
In 1, 2, 3.

1522
00:51:49,270 --> 00:51:50,409
(It's 2 to 2, so they have a rematch.)

1523
00:51:50,410 --> 00:51:51,910
- In 1, 2, 3.
- In 1, 2, 3.

1524
00:51:52,940 --> 00:51:53,940
Three.

1525
00:51:54,340 --> 00:51:55,779
- Is he out, then?
- You're paying.

1526
00:51:55,780 --> 00:51:56,879
- I'm out, right?
- No, you're paying.

1527
00:51:56,880 --> 00:51:58,649
- I'm out.
- He's out.

1528
00:51:58,650 --> 00:51:59,850
- Come on.
- All right.

1529
00:52:00,020 --> 00:52:02,920
This time, the odd one out will pay.

1530
00:52:03,120 --> 00:52:04,120
If only one person is different,

1531
00:52:04,121 --> 00:52:05,519
- he has to pay.
- Yes.

1532
00:52:05,520 --> 00:52:07,459
- Let me say this beforehand.
- We...

1533
00:52:07,460 --> 00:52:08,930
- I'm going to sit.
- I'm going to sit.

1534
00:52:10,030 --> 00:52:11,459
- I'll stand.
- You'll stand?

1535
00:52:11,460 --> 00:52:12,560
- Yes.
- Okay.

1536
00:52:12,760 --> 00:52:14,699
(The brothers say that they'll sit, )

1537
00:52:14,700 --> 00:52:16,500
(and Yeon Seok says he'll stand.)

1538
00:52:16,570 --> 00:52:18,470
- Okay.
- In 1, 2, 3.

1539
00:52:18,840 --> 00:52:19,870
Okay.

1540
00:52:20,200 --> 00:52:21,540
In 1, 2, 3.

1541
00:52:21,810 --> 00:52:22,839
(Slouching)

1542
00:52:22,840 --> 00:52:23,870
You...

1543
00:52:24,470 --> 00:52:26,579
- Thanks, Yeon Seok.
- You were late.

1544
00:52:26,580 --> 00:52:28,250
That was so lame just now.

1545
00:52:28,580 --> 00:52:29,980
- Jeez.
- Let's order everything.

1546
00:52:30,210 --> 00:52:32,050
I feel like those brothers scammed me.

1547
00:52:34,450 --> 00:52:35,819
Are you sure about this?

1548
00:52:35,820 --> 00:52:37,019
- Of course.
- That's expensive.

1549
00:52:37,020 --> 00:52:38,490
- Thanks for the food.
- It's expensive.

1550
00:52:40,360 --> 00:52:41,630
(He spots the owner.)

1551
00:52:42,190 --> 00:52:43,959
I was here last time, and it was so good...

1552
00:52:43,960 --> 00:52:46,130
- that I came back.
- Thank you.

1553
00:52:47,430 --> 00:52:49,500
- Thanks for the food, Yeon Shik.
- Sure.

1554
00:52:49,830 --> 00:52:50,900
I think it'll be tasty.

1555
00:52:51,500 --> 00:52:53,600
Se Hyeong once said...

1556
00:52:53,870 --> 00:52:57,070
that we should open a pork rib restaurant.

1557
00:52:57,510 --> 00:52:59,480
- Brother Pork Ribs.
- Brother Pork Ribs.

1558
00:53:00,110 --> 00:53:01,349
He suggested it.

1559
00:53:01,350 --> 00:53:04,149
We could open it in the mountain with some charcoal fire going.

1560
00:53:04,150 --> 00:53:05,349
(The brothers' big dream)

1561
00:53:05,350 --> 00:53:07,119
- Brother Pork Ribs?
- Because...

1562
00:53:07,120 --> 00:53:10,420
You never know. You might actually do it.

1563
00:53:10,650 --> 00:53:12,489
- We might.
- You never know.

1564
00:53:12,490 --> 00:53:14,829
And it's nice to have a strong...

1565
00:53:14,830 --> 00:53:15,830
brotherly bond.

1566
00:53:15,831 --> 00:53:18,229
- And they're both in entertainment.
- "Brotherly bond."

1567
00:53:18,230 --> 00:53:19,700
It's wholesome.

1568
00:53:19,900 --> 00:53:20,999
You can rely on each other.

1569
00:53:21,000 --> 00:53:22,230
- That's true.
- It is nice.

1570
00:53:22,530 --> 00:53:23,930
It's especially good...

1571
00:53:24,200 --> 00:53:26,500
because we have the same job while we're brothers.

1572
00:53:26,840 --> 00:53:27,869
The things we can't say...

1573
00:53:27,870 --> 00:53:28,909
- even to our colleagues.
- Right.

1574
00:53:28,910 --> 00:53:30,710
But we can talk about it because we're family.

1575
00:53:30,910 --> 00:53:33,279
Having someone you can entirely open up to...

1576
00:53:33,280 --> 00:53:34,410
Right.

1577
00:53:34,780 --> 00:53:37,080
It'll give you some comfort.

1578
00:53:37,150 --> 00:53:38,280
We depend on each other.

1579
00:53:38,780 --> 00:53:40,049
- Here's our food.
- This is pho.

1580
00:53:40,050 --> 00:53:42,120
- I also ordered pho.
- Pho.

1581
00:53:42,420 --> 00:53:43,919
- Oh, it's a clear broth.
- Thank you.

1582
00:53:43,920 --> 00:53:45,990
- It's unique, isn't it?
- This is...

1583
00:53:46,390 --> 00:53:48,589
- It looks good.
- You chose egg noodles.

1584
00:53:48,590 --> 00:53:50,260
- That looks scrumptious.
- Vinegar.

1585
00:53:51,300 --> 00:53:52,730
Add fish sauce.

1586
00:53:53,800 --> 00:53:55,200
- That's good.
- Let's see.

1587
00:53:55,600 --> 00:53:56,600
It's great.

1588
00:53:56,601 --> 00:53:59,440
(They take turns and try it.)

1589
00:54:01,200 --> 00:54:02,739
(Moaning)

1590
00:54:02,740 --> 00:54:03,970
- It makes me happy.
- That's good.

1591
00:54:05,310 --> 00:54:06,610
- It's really good.
- Yes.

1592
00:54:07,680 --> 00:54:08,780
(Proud)

1593
00:54:11,550 --> 00:54:12,819
(Yeon Seok wraps it in coriander and tries it.)

1594
00:54:12,820 --> 00:54:13,880
Good.

1595
00:54:14,990 --> 00:54:15,990
(Slurping)

1596
00:54:16,620 --> 00:54:17,620
(Slurping)

1597
00:54:18,960 --> 00:54:20,290
(Moaning)

1598
00:54:21,190 --> 00:54:23,790
(Completely absorbed)

1599
00:54:24,490 --> 00:54:26,299
(What's their next spare time spot...)

1600
00:54:26,300 --> 00:54:28,599
(that they'll go with full bellies?)

1601
00:54:28,600 --> 00:54:29,900
It's a unique name.

1602
00:54:30,730 --> 00:54:31,969
Gong Gyeok.

1603
00:54:31,970 --> 00:54:33,169
- Gong Gyeok?
- Gong Gyeok?

1604
00:54:33,170 --> 00:54:35,039
- That's the name?
- Gong Gyeok?

1605
00:54:35,040 --> 00:54:36,209
There are many people with the family name Gong.

1606
00:54:36,210 --> 00:54:38,009
- So, his first name is Gyeok?
- Yes.

1607
00:54:38,010 --> 00:54:40,079
"My dream is to close up shop."

1608
00:54:40,080 --> 00:54:41,109
- Close up?
- What?

1609
00:54:41,110 --> 00:54:42,480
- He wants to quit.
- Close up shop?

1610
00:54:42,550 --> 00:54:45,820
"With my friends, a delivery rider and a cat butler,"

1611
00:54:46,020 --> 00:54:48,119
"I want to throw away my day job and travel the country."

1612
00:54:48,120 --> 00:54:50,389
"We want to live and die..."

1613
00:54:50,390 --> 00:54:53,090
"for the joy of meeting elders everywhere."

1614
00:54:53,160 --> 00:54:54,160
- What?
- What?

1615
00:54:54,161 --> 00:54:56,190
"Please give us strength."

1616
00:54:56,630 --> 00:54:58,600
So, he wants to quit...

1617
00:54:58,900 --> 00:55:00,830
and pursue his dream.

1618
00:55:00,960 --> 00:55:02,030
We're almost there.

1619
00:55:02,500 --> 00:55:03,570
Is this it?

1620
00:55:03,830 --> 00:55:04,840
"Jam space?"

1621
00:55:05,600 --> 00:55:08,039
This is it. Tiger Jam Space.

1622
00:55:08,040 --> 00:55:09,909
Oh, he said something about traveling everywhere.

1623
00:55:09,910 --> 00:55:11,209
- Right?
- He must be in a band.

1624
00:55:11,210 --> 00:55:12,610
He has a day job,

1625
00:55:12,910 --> 00:55:14,909
but he comes to a practice room...

1626
00:55:14,910 --> 00:55:16,909
- to practice.
- That must be it.

1627
00:55:16,910 --> 00:55:19,320
I think this is it.

1628
00:55:19,580 --> 00:55:20,649
(Along the long corridor)

1629
00:55:20,650 --> 00:55:22,220
- Hello!
- Hello!

1630
00:55:22,490 --> 00:55:23,490
This is the one.

1631
00:55:23,650 --> 00:55:24,819
Who's Mr. Gong Gyeok?

1632
00:55:24,820 --> 00:55:26,190
- I'm Gong Gyeok.
- Okay.

1633
00:55:26,560 --> 00:55:27,589
(The Whenever Guest, Gong Gyeok, and his 2 friends)

1634
00:55:27,590 --> 00:55:28,760
- Hello.
- Hello.

1635
00:55:29,390 --> 00:55:30,859
(Gong Gyeok, second Whenever Guest)

1636
00:55:30,860 --> 00:55:32,959
(With Myoung Ji Su and Yeon Gwang Mo)

1637
00:55:32,960 --> 00:55:34,400
Hello, everyone.

1638
00:55:34,700 --> 00:55:35,799
Nice to meet you.

1639
00:55:35,800 --> 00:55:37,299
(Gong Gyeok, Myoung Ji Su, and Yeon Gwang Mo)

1640
00:55:37,300 --> 00:55:38,440
What's that tiger?

1641
00:55:39,800 --> 00:55:41,370
- We love tigers.
- Born in the Year of the Tiger?

1642
00:55:41,510 --> 00:55:42,909
- I was.
- Really?

1643
00:55:42,910 --> 00:55:44,209
I was born in the Year of the Tiger.

1644
00:55:44,210 --> 00:55:45,439
- What year is that?
- In 1986.

1645
00:55:45,440 --> 00:55:46,780
I was also born in 1986.

1646
00:55:46,940 --> 00:55:48,350
- Team Tiger.
- We're the same age.

1647
00:55:48,580 --> 00:55:49,879
We were born in the same year.

1648
00:55:49,880 --> 00:55:51,649
Is Gong Gyeok your real name?

1649
00:55:51,650 --> 00:55:53,379
That's my stage name.

1650
00:55:53,380 --> 00:55:56,419
My real name is Gong Dong Min.

1651
00:55:56,420 --> 00:55:58,290
- Dong Min.
- I knew it.

1652
00:55:58,360 --> 00:56:00,690
Your parents couldn't have named you Gong Gyeok.

1653
00:56:00,820 --> 00:56:02,889
- It was his stage name.
- Yes.

1654
00:56:02,890 --> 00:56:05,599
I needed my parents' approval to change my real name.

1655
00:56:05,600 --> 00:56:06,999
You want to actually change your name?

1656
00:56:07,000 --> 00:56:09,069
Yes, I wanted to, but I couldn't.

1657
00:56:09,070 --> 00:56:11,369
Perhaps I could...

1658
00:56:11,370 --> 00:56:14,299
make it my real name in the future.

1659
00:56:14,300 --> 00:56:16,569
- Are the three of you friends?
- A team?

1660
00:56:16,570 --> 00:56:18,539
- Or band members?
- We're a band.

1661
00:56:18,540 --> 00:56:20,180
- Should we introduce ourselves?
- Yes, please.

1662
00:56:20,710 --> 00:56:21,949
- What's the name of the band?
- Hi, everyone.

1663
00:56:21,950 --> 00:56:24,410
- We're the Far East Asian Tigers.
- Roar!

1664
00:56:24,550 --> 00:56:25,550
- Roar!
- Roar!

1665
00:56:27,420 --> 00:56:29,090
- Far East Asian Tigers.
- Far East Asian Tigers.

1666
00:56:29,220 --> 00:56:30,590
That's an impressive name.

1667
00:56:30,790 --> 00:56:32,059
Hence, the tigers.

1668
00:56:32,060 --> 00:56:35,190
It's because we rarely say "Far East" nowadays.

1669
00:56:38,600 --> 00:56:40,559
(Drum, Yeon Gwang Mo)

1670
00:56:40,560 --> 00:56:42,429
(Vocalist and guitar, Myoung Ji Su)

1671
00:56:42,430 --> 00:56:44,129
(Guitar, Kang Yong Hyeok)

1672
00:56:44,130 --> 00:56:46,040
(Bass, Gong Gyeok)

1673
00:56:46,900 --> 00:56:50,009
(From daycare centers...)

1674
00:56:50,010 --> 00:56:51,839
(to elementary schools, )

1675
00:56:51,840 --> 00:56:53,580
(middle schools, and high schools)

1676
00:56:53,780 --> 00:56:57,150
(And they've performed at local festivals.)

1677
00:56:57,910 --> 00:56:59,879
(They dominated major rock festivals...)

1678
00:56:59,880 --> 00:57:01,020
(with their tiger-like sounds.)

1679
00:57:02,020 --> 00:57:04,920
(A band that sings of eternal youth)

1680
00:57:05,260 --> 00:57:07,090
(Far East Asian Tigers)

1681
00:57:07,590 --> 00:57:09,159
Oh, I've heard of you!

1682
00:57:09,160 --> 00:57:10,459
- Really?
- I've heard of them.

1683
00:57:10,460 --> 00:57:12,099
I said their songs were good to someone,

1684
00:57:12,100 --> 00:57:14,299
and he said the band was already popular.

1685
00:57:14,300 --> 00:57:15,569
- They're popular.
- That's right.

1686
00:57:15,570 --> 00:57:17,969
They're pretty experienced in the indie scene.

1687
00:57:17,970 --> 00:57:21,069
It looks like you guys are pretty famous.

1688
00:57:21,070 --> 00:57:22,739
Where do you usually perform?

1689
00:57:22,740 --> 00:57:24,939
We go wherever they ask us.

1690
00:57:24,940 --> 00:57:26,139
Everywhere in the country.

1691
00:57:26,140 --> 00:57:27,209
- Oh, you go anywhere?
- Yes.

1692
00:57:27,210 --> 00:57:28,409
- The whole country?
- Yes.

1693
00:57:28,410 --> 00:57:31,279
Was there a particularly memorable performance?

1694
00:57:31,280 --> 00:57:32,320
Inje?

1695
00:57:32,620 --> 00:57:34,319
- Inje?
- What about Inje?

1696
00:57:34,320 --> 00:57:39,290
It was a performance that marked our big break.

1697
00:57:39,390 --> 00:57:41,019
We're better-known to people as the Allowance Band...

1698
00:57:41,020 --> 00:57:42,389
- than the Far East Asian Tigers.
- Right.

1699
00:57:42,390 --> 00:57:44,259
- The Allowance Band.
- What does that mean?

1700
00:57:44,260 --> 00:57:45,260
Did you get an allowance?

1701
00:57:45,700 --> 00:57:48,500
(During the Inje Fall Flower Festival)

1702
00:57:49,530 --> 00:57:52,140
(The elders gathered when they heard music.)

1703
00:57:53,370 --> 00:57:55,710
(They started throwing allowances onto the stage.)

1704
00:57:57,240 --> 00:57:58,280
Stop giving us allowances!

1705
00:57:58,880 --> 00:58:00,139
(They had to ask them to stop in the end.)

1706
00:58:00,140 --> 00:58:01,380
Please don't.

1707
00:58:01,750 --> 00:58:02,910
(Giving them an allowance and running)

1708
00:58:04,780 --> 00:58:07,420
(They kept giving them allowances.)

1709
00:58:07,820 --> 00:58:10,249
When you get 50 dollars, you have to do something.

1710
00:58:10,250 --> 00:58:11,390
Everyone, jump!

1711
00:58:12,490 --> 00:58:16,060
(Whatever. Let's just rock and roll together.)

1712
00:58:17,330 --> 00:58:19,860
(They became one at the festival with allowances and music.)

1713
00:58:20,200 --> 00:58:21,600
They gave you allowances.

1714
00:58:22,000 --> 00:58:23,369
- On the stage.
- On the stage.

1715
00:58:23,370 --> 00:58:25,039
They climbed the stage?

1716
00:58:25,040 --> 00:58:26,500
That's so cool. That's youth.

1717
00:58:26,640 --> 00:58:29,209
If you were born in 1986, you're the same age as Se Chan.

1718
00:58:29,210 --> 00:58:31,139
Yes, we were both born in the Year of the Tiger.

1719
00:58:31,140 --> 00:58:32,909
When band members...

1720
00:58:32,910 --> 00:58:34,540
- turn 30, - Yes.

1721
00:58:34,810 --> 00:58:36,609
I hear that it's a period where you have to make decisions,

1722
00:58:36,610 --> 00:58:38,779
especially in the indie scene.

1723
00:58:38,780 --> 00:58:42,119
That's true. As I got married...

1724
00:58:42,120 --> 00:58:43,349
- You're married?
- Oh, you're married.

1725
00:58:43,350 --> 00:58:45,689
Yes, I'm married and have two daughters.

1726
00:58:45,690 --> 00:58:48,289
- What?
- How long have you been married?

1727
00:58:48,290 --> 00:58:49,930
I got married in 2017.

1728
00:58:50,190 --> 00:58:51,729
- It's been about ten years.
- This year, my first daughter...

1729
00:58:51,730 --> 00:58:53,229
is entering elementary school,

1730
00:58:53,230 --> 00:58:55,929
and my second one is entering kindergarten.

1731
00:58:55,930 --> 00:58:58,269
- He doesn't look his age.
- So,

1732
00:58:58,270 --> 00:58:59,840
the practice room is...

1733
00:59:00,000 --> 00:59:02,770
one way to make a living so that I can keep performing.

1734
00:59:02,940 --> 00:59:05,079
My goal is...

1735
00:59:05,080 --> 00:59:07,010
to close up this practice room...

1736
00:59:07,140 --> 00:59:09,249
- Oh, close up.
- so that I can prove it...

1737
00:59:09,250 --> 00:59:11,379
- with our music.
- You want to prove yourself.

1738
00:59:11,380 --> 00:59:12,919
My goal is to prove...

1739
00:59:12,920 --> 00:59:14,449
that you can still make a living...

1740
00:59:14,450 --> 00:59:17,120
while performing across the country.

1741
00:59:17,450 --> 00:59:19,589
So, Gyeok runs the jam space.

1742
00:59:19,590 --> 00:59:22,429
What about the other two? Do you have side jobs?

1743
00:59:22,430 --> 00:59:26,330
I make deliveries to make a living.

